headline: Supermicro commencing shipments of servers featuring Intel Xeon 6900s
summary: Supermicro (SMCI) announced it is commencing shipments of max-performance servers featuring Intel (INTC) Xeon 6900 series processors with P-cores. “The systems now shipping in volume promise to unlock new capabilities and levels of performance for our customers around the world, featuring low latency, maximum I/O expansion providing high throughput with 256 performance cores per system, 12 memory channels per CPU with MRDIMM support, and high performance EDSFF storage options,” said Charles Lian
